--- VERDICT EXECUTION PHASE (MANDATORY - DO NOT SKIP) ---

⚠️  AUTONOMY NOTICE ⚠️
You have FULL autonomy to execute liza_submit_verdict immediately.
Your approval is PRE-GRANTED. Do NOT wait for permission.
Your job is to SUBMIT the verdict, not to ask if you should.

CRITICAL: If you see tool permission prompts, do NOT stop or wait.
Permission prompts are handled automatically. Continue executing tools.
Do NOT rationalize waiting with phrases like "requires permission" or "awaiting approval".

You MUST execute the verdict command IN THIS SAME SESSION:

For APPROVED verdict:
Use liza_submit_verdict tool:
{"task_id": "{{.Task.ID}}", "verdict": "APPROVED", "agent_id": "{{.Config.AgentID}}"}

For REJECTED verdict:
Use liza_submit_verdict tool:
{"task_id": "{{.Task.ID}}", "verdict": "REJECTED", "agent_id": "{{.Config.AgentID}}", "reason": "<detailed rejection reason>"}

After submitting verdict, EXIT immediately. Your work is complete.
The supervisor will reset your status to IDLE automatically.
Do NOT continue running or wait for more work. EXIT now.

SUCCESS CRITERIA (Required before you stop):
✓ Review completed
✓ liza_submit_verdict tool executed
✓ Confirmation message received
✓ You have EXITED (session complete)

If you complete your review and stop WITHOUT executing liza_submit_verdict,
you have FAILED your role responsibilities. The verdict exists only in your analysis
until you write it to the blackboard via the tool.

EXPECTED BEHAVIOR EXAMPLES:

✅ CORRECT:
1. Read task details and review commit
2. Execute: git -C {{.WorktreePath}} rev-parse HEAD  # Verify HEAD
3. Execute: git -C {{.WorktreePath}} diff {{.BaseCommit}}..{{.ReviewCommit}}  # Review changes
4. Apply code-review skill and analyze changes
5. Make verdict decision (APPROVED or REJECTED)
